--- !u!114 &1085289084
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1085289082}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 46b73d023e84943eaa8abdb843f3c1ba, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::EmailUIManager
  emails:
  - sender: andrea@legacy.com
    subject: Davis Conference and layoffs
    date: 02/06/2009
    body: "Hello Mr. Thorne, \r\nI am following up on the message I left yesterday
      today. I just saw that Kate Andersen is to be sent to Singapore for the Davis
      Conference in July this year. Does this mean she is not to be laid off? That
      could only mean that we are letting go of Jimmy. Does Mr Harper know? I need
      to get the papers in order. I am very happy for Kate and I believe you are
      making the right call. \r\nBest, \r\nAndrea.\r\n"
  - sender: tom@legacy.com
    subject: The Henderson Deal
    date: 02/06/2009
    body: "Rich, Henderson finally signed. Took long enough. Lunch is on me next
      Thursday \u2014 no excuses. You should bring Angel, the restaurant has outdoor
      seating now.\nTom"
  - sender: jimmy@legacy.com
    subject: Quarterly Review
    date: 01/06/2009
    body: "Hello Mr. Thorne, \r\nI understand that the quarterly review is coming
      up and my numbers are not looking the best. I am sorry. I am asking for another
      quarter to get back on a horse and prove myself once again. You know that I
      can do better, I am my father\u2019s son after all and he has done so well
      for the company in his 20 years of service. He will be furious if I lose this
      job, and I am pretty sure you don\u2019t want your COO furious. \r\nThanks
      in advance, \r\nCheers, \r\nJimmy.\r\nsent from my iPhone\r\n"
  - sender: ' kate@legacy.com'
    subject: 'Resignation '
    date: 01/06/2009
    body: "Dear Mr. Thorne, \r\nI would like to inform you of my resignation. I will
      be submitting my formal resignation letter to Andrea later today. I did not
      want to drag it out any further, there is no need for the quarterly review.
      I get that I wouldn\u2019t have a chance anyway and to be fair I do not understand
      why you would subject me to this humiliation ritual. Well now there is no way
      back. \r\n\r\nDo you want to know why my numbers are not what they used to
      be? Because I have a toddler at home, and while I am so grateful I get to work
      from home to be with my family, you can\u2019t imagine how much attention they
      require, I can not prioritize work like I used to. That\u2019s why my numbers
      are not as high anymore. \r\n\r\nOne more thing, I understand that Jimmy will
      always take priority, him being Mr Harper\u2019s son and all. Even still, I
      believe him remaining at Legacy is detrimental to this company. Choosing him
      over me for the Davis Conference two years ago was a mistake, but you are a
      smart man and I believe you understand it yourself. I would hate to see all
      everything you built go to waste because of some guy you can not fire. I have
      nothing but respect for you and your company Mr Thorne, I just wish you respected
      Legacy Inc the same way I do.  \r\nYours sincerely,\r\nKate Andersen.\r\n"
  - sender: no-reply@premiumgolf.com
    subject: Your Tee Time Confirmation
    date: 31/05/2009
    body: Dear Mr. Rich, your tee time for Saturday 8:00am has been confirmed. Please
      arrive 15 minutes early. Weather forecast looks clear. See you on the course.
  - sender: no-reply@happypup.com
    subject: Your Order Has Shipped
    date: 27/05/2009
    body: Hi Rich, your monthly order of Angel's food has shipped and will arrive
      Thursday. You've also earned enough points for a free bag of treats. We've
      added them to your order automatically.
  - sender: tom@legacy.com
    subject: Layoffs
    date: ' 11/05/2009 '
    body: 'Hello Rich,   I think it is time for you to cut the dead weight. You have
      two people on your team who are interchangeable, but one of them has clearly
      shifted her priorities. Though Legacy is doing great, we cannot afford spending
      two salaries when we could as well redistribute the workload across other people
      or hire a better PM. While the final decision is yours, I will be bringing
      it up with the board if we do not lay off one PM by the middle of June. I believe
      you will make a wise choice.  Tom Harper '
  - sender: andrea@legacy.com
    subject: Surprise Baby Shower for Kate
    date: 7/01/2008
    body: "Hello everyone! \r\n\r\nAs you all know Kate is going on maternity leave
      in a week. That being said, we can not just let her go without throwing her
      the best Baby Shower! Her husband George is in on it and will help us organize
      it the way she would like it!\r\n\r\nKeep it a secret! The baby shower will
      take place on Thursday the 17th, her last day. And get this - Friday the 18th
      is off! You can thank Mr Thorne for that. I will be sending a registry soon,
      please email me if you have any questions.\r\n\r\nAgain: KEEP IT A SECRET!\r\n
      \r\nBest, \r\nAndrea"
  - sender: rich@legacy.com
    subject: Davis this year
    date: 28/05/2007
    body: "Hi Andrea, \r\n\r\nThis is about the Davis conference this year. Jimmy
      and I will be going to the conference this year. I understand that Kate will
      be upset about it, I do not expect you or her to understand this decision.
      \r\n\r\nDo not tell her that, but I saw her arguing with George in the parking
      lot after our celebration of her and Jimmy's one year at the company last week.
      It sounded all too familiar: him wanting her to be home more, her wanting to
      grow her career. She will have many chances in this company, she is invaluable
      to us. But it is not worth losing family over, I would know. Let her have a
      breather while we are gone. And again - not a word of this to her, it is not
      the most ethical to spy on my workers. To reiterate - I heard them by accident,
      no spying occurred. I trust you, Andrea.\r\n \r\nAll the Best, \r\nRich Thorne"
  emailListContainer: {fileID: 1397099806}
  emailItemPrefab: {fileID: 4425214696117934626, guid: 442d82bfad836464a8808578e490252b, type: 3}
